{title: The Nail Scarred Hand}
{artist: Carl Smith}
{composer: unknown}

[C]Have you failed in your plan of your storm caused life
Place your [G7]hand in the nail scarred [C]hand
Are you weary and worn from its toil and strife
Place your [G7]hand in the nail scarred [C]hand
Place your [F]hand in the nail scarred [C]hand
Place your [D7]hand in the nail scarred [G7]hand
He will [C]keep to the end He's your dearest [F]friend
Place your [G7]hand in the nail scarred [C]hand
Are you walking alone through the shadows dim
Place your [G7]hand in the nail scarred [C]hand
Christ will comfort your heart put your trust in Him
Place your [G7]hand in the nail scarred [C]hand
Repeat #2
Would you follow the will of the risen Lord
Place your [G7]hand in the nail scarred [C]hand
Would you live in the light of His blessed Word
Place your [G7]hand in the nail scared [C]hand
Repeat #2
Is you soul burdened down with the load of sin
Place your [G7]hand in the nail scarred [C]hand
Throw your heart open wide let the Savior in
Place your [G7]hand in the nail scarred [C]hand
Repeat #2